			<div class="content" id="post-content-2167977">
									

<p>Others have addressed the main points about this so I won't do some line by line. But I did want to note that I know where you're coming from on this, I've had similar feelings in the past, I actually mostly agree with your views on what's good. But it's not that the things you're talking about are &quot;rules&quot; in the idea of things being explicitly forbidden, but rather that it's a &quot;rule of thumb&quot;, in that it's how the community will respond to certain things.</p>
<p>You almost never see cross-linking articles, useful items, or old-style articles succeed anymore these days. But that's about the COMMUNITY, not about the rules. If it were staff or some special delegation choosing what stays and what goes, then I'd agree with you actually. At that point the rules should be changed and those things be allowed because that'd be ridiculous. But since it's the community at large voting things out, then it's just a matter of being wistful for the old days and wishing these youngsters shared your values.</p>
<p>It's like seeing a movie that you loved get bad box office takings and get negative reviews(cough Serenity cough, cough Ender's Game cough). You can't be upset at the industry, just the general public for not liking what you like for whatever reason. But you're just one person in a crowd, and the crowd probably doesn't agree with you on most things.</p>
<p>If you leave, just keep in mind you're leaving because you don't find SCP articles as interesting as they used to be. We didn't drive you out or push you away, you yourself became bored with it. And that's fine. Interests change over time, and sometimes our interests change on us into things we no longer care for (cough Star Wars cough). It's life. If you stick around then cool. If you leave, then ok. Have fun wherever else you go.</p>

							</div>

								
