														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2172403">
									

<p>I said some of my thoughts in my response to Soulless, but I'll clear up my exact opinion here.</p>
<p>I almost totally agree with this. I'm also not that surprised that so many of the older members disagreed vehemently with what you had to say. This site used to be filled with great articles, both simple and complex. Nowadays, people jump all over you if you have an idea even similar to something already done. And forget trying to do something that isn't completely alien and makes no sense at all. For instance, SCP-334, one of the most well-done articles I've seen to date, was downvoted solely on the basis that it was a cat. Seriously. And this is by Bright, arguably the single most popular and experienced active member to date. Why can't it be a cat? Does everything have to be a platypus or echidna or obscure mollusk? It's as if the oldest members have this idea in their heads of everything having to be completely original or downvote. But somewhere along the line, &quot;originial&quot; and &quot;flat-out bizzare&quot; meant the same thing, which shouldn't be the case. It's like people have an attatchment to the older articles, but if someone makes something similar, they automatically hate it. Really, the only thing that I disagreed with you on was the -j. (Come on, man, that was adorable.)</p>

