			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2172460">
									

<p>Most people don't have attachments to old articles, though. In fact a majority of the userbase despises most of the older articles that no longer measure up to our standards. The only reason those articles are lingering around such high ratings is mostly due to rating inertia, where an article accrues tons of upvotes from ye olden days that take tons of downvotes to counter.<br />
I do agree that disliking an article <em>solely</em> because it uses a concept that's already been done before is kinda dumb, but if it doesn't execute that concept in a unique or interesting way to distinguish it from the all the other articles that use it, it's justified. The cat thing with 334 is dumb, though.<br />
My biggest point of contention is with your view regarding Tales. Yes, they <em>seem</em> convoluted and unapproachable at first, but if you actually take the time to read a few, they won't. They're no more confusing or reliant on established canons as a majority of SCP articles are, and there is no tale on this entire site that takes &quot;hours to read&quot;. Series, maybe, but not individual tales. If you continue to hold this view you're gonna be missing out on some of the highest quality works on the site.</p>

