			<div class="content" id="post-content-2213309">
									

<blockquote>
<p>but members are becoming afraid to publish an article, especially an SCP.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I feel like this can actually be a good thing, if it gets people to use the forums and/or chat correctly. I'm still relatively terrified when I post things to the site.</p>
<p>If someone's scared of posting, they should figure out <em>why</em> they're scared, and take the steps to rectify that if they can. Usually that involves learning to write at the standards of the site (which are, admittedly, pretty high. Most contributors have college-level or above writing experience).</p>
<p>People need to be willing to learn here. Everyone grows at some point. I remember my first post; I didn't get any feedback whatsoever, it was a generic magic object object what crazied you to death, and part of the experiment log included the phrase &quot;scream recorded issuing from bathroom&quot;.</p>
<p>If someone really has what it takes to create material consistently up to the site's quality standard, then they won't mind putting in the effort to hit that mark. This site should be a hobby&#8212;the moment it's not fun anymore, that's an indication that a writing break is needed. Work on something else, do some reading, go for a walk, whatever.</p>
<p>Also, in regards to the tales&#8230; we've got hundreds of those, varying in rating, and frankly it's always more admirable to work your way up to standard rather than hoping for standards to be lowered to accommodate those who haven't gotten there yet.</p>

