<blockquote>
<p>I suppose it isn't now, but members are becoming afraid to publish an article, especially an SCP.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>According to who? You? Either detail the extensive outreach you've done to come to this conclusion, or quit acting as though you speak for the community in general.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>But I would like it if we slackened up on the strictness on tales.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I can't speak for the community, but speaking personally as a member of staff and both Forum and Site Critique teams: No. Absolutely not. In fact, tales, in my opinion, are not held to a high enough standard, due to their lower readership. The core value of this site is quality. We're not here to preserve feelings.</p>

